1 - editoronfig- EditorConfig helps maintain consistent coding style of multiples
developers working on same project across various editors and IDEs.the editoronfig
projects consists of a file formate for define coding styles and a collection of
text editor plugins that enable editors to read the file formate and adhere to
define styles.editoronfig files are easily readable and they work nicely with version
control system.
example-


root = true
 
[*]
indent_style = space
indent_size = 4
end_of_line = lf
charset = utf-8
trim_trailing_whitespace = true # doesn't work yet
insert_final_newline = true # doesn't work yet
